CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 6</H1></CENTER>    
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>We then, as       
workers together with him, beseech you also that ye receive not the grace of    
ELOHIYM in vain.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD> 
<P>(For he saith, I have heard thee in a time accepted, and in the day of       
salvation have I succoured thee: behold, now is the accepted time; behold, now  
is the day of salvation.)</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4> 
</TD><TD><P>Giving no offence in any thing, that the ministry be not blamed:</P>
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>But in all things 
approving ourselves as the ministers of ELOHIYM, in much patience, in           
afflictions, in necessities, in distresses,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A  
NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>In stripes, in imprisonments, in tumults, in      
labours, in watchings, in fastings;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6> 
<H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>By pureness, by knowledge, by longsuffering, by kindness, 
by the Holy Ghost, by love unfeigned,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A        
NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>By the word of truth, by the power of ELOHIYM, by 
the armour of righteousness on the right hand and on the left,</P></TD></TR><TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>By honour and dishonour, by     
evil report and good report: as deceivers, and yet true;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD   
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>As unknown, and yet well known; as  
dying, and, behold, we live; as chastened, and not killed;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>As sorrowful, yet alway           
rejoicing; as poor, yet making many rich; as having nothing, and yet possessing 
all things.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P> 
O ye Corinthians, our mouth is open unto you, our heart is enlarged.</P></TD>   
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>Ye are not           
straitened in us, but ye are straitened in your own bowels.</P></TD></TR><TR>   
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>Now for a recompence in the   
same, (I speak as unto my children,) be ye also enlarged.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD  
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>Be ye not unequally yoked         
together with unbelievers: for what fellowship hath righteousness with          
unrighteousness? and what communion hath light with darkness?</P></TD></TR><TR> 
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>And what concord hath         
MASHIYACH with Belial? or what part hath he that believeth with an infidel?</P> 
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>And what        
agreement hath the temple of YHVH with idols? for ye are the temple of the      
living EL; as hath said, I will dwell in them, and walk in them; and I will be  
their ELOHIYM, and they shall be my people.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A  
NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>Wherefore come out from among them, and be ye   
separate, saith YHVH, and touch not the unclean thing; and I will receive       
you.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>And     
will be a Father unto you, and ye shall be my sons and daughters, saith the EL  
SHADDAY.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This Software is copyright 2000 by John M.    
